{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides"]]},"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Composable Architecture is under constant development, and we are always looking for ways to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"simplify the library, and make it more powerful. This version of the library only introduced new"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"APIs and did not deprecate any existing APIs."}]},{"type":"aside","name":"Important","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Before following this migration guide be sure you have fully migrated to the newest","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"tools of version 1.9. See ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" for more information.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"important"},{"text":"Sharing state","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Sharing-state"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The new tools added are concerned with allowing one to seamlessly share state with many parts of an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"application that is easy to understand, and most importantly, testable. See the dedicated","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SharingState","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" article for more information on how to use these new tools.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To share state in one feature with another feature, simply use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Shared"},{"type":"text","text":" property wrapper:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@ObservableState","struct State {","  @Shared var signUpData: SignUpData","  \/\/ ...","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This will require that ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SignUpData"},{"text":" be passed in from the parent, and any changes made to this state","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"will be instantly observed by all features holding onto it.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Further, there are persistence strategies one can employ in ","type":"text"},{"code":"@Shared","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". For example, if you want any","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"changes of ","type":"text"},{"code":"signUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to be automatically persisted to the file system you can use","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"fileStorage(_:decoder:encoder:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and specify a URL:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@ObservableState","struct State {","  @Shared(.fileStorage(URL(\/* ... *\/) var signUpData = SignUpData()","  \/\/ ...","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Upon app launch the "},{"code":"signUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will be populated from disk, and any changes made to "},{"code":"signUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will automatically be persisted to disk. Further, if the disk version changes, all instances of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"signUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" in the application will automatically update."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"There is another persistence strategy for storing simple data types in user defaults, called","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"appStorage","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". It can refer to a value in user defaults by a string","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"key:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["@ObservableState ","struct State {","  @Shared(.appStorage(\"isOn\")) var isOn = false","  \/\/ ...","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Similar to ","type":"text"},{"code":"fileStorage(_:decoder:encoder:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", upon launch of the application the initial","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"value of ","type":"text"},{"code":"isOn","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will be populated from user defaults, and any change to ","type":"text"},{"code":"isOn","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will be automatically","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"persisted to user defaults. Further, if the user defaults value changes, all instances of ","type":"text"},{"code":"isOn","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in the application will automatically update.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"That is the basics of sharing data. Be sure to see the dedicated "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SharingState","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" article"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for more detailed information."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/migratingto1.10"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Update your code to make use of the new state sharing tools in the library, such as the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Shared"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"property wrapper, and the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"appStorage"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fileStorage"},{"type":"text","text":" persistence strategies."}],"identifier":{"interfaceLangu